[00:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There are a few new updates from the last SCAIL-2&nbsp; video. Firstly, GGUF files are out. Secondly,&nbsp;&nbsp; there is this new masking node that will allow us&nbsp; to do a more precise and controlled segmentation&nbsp;&nbsp; of the subjects, plus it includes the capability&nbsp; of MSR, or multi-subject referencing. And lastly,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a new sampler node that allows us to push the&nbsp; video length through the 81 frames cap, as you&nbsp;&nbsp; have seen at the start of the video. I will show&nbsp; how I set it up in a minute. Let\'s take a quick&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'look at the workflow components. Models are loaded&nbsp; here. Download links, including the GGUF models&nbsp;&nbsp; are provided in the red node. Here is our image&nbsp; loading, some settings and sampling group. Then&nbsp;&nbsp; here is the interpolation, upscaling and saving&nbsp; group nodes. And here are the image and video&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'segmentation group nodes. And lastly, the nodes&nbsp; to merge the videos together into a single video&nbsp;&nbsp; for demonstration. This group can be disabled.&nbsp; Okay. Here is the new SCAIL-2 Identity Tracker&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'node. You will need to manually install it. And&nbsp; here is the new SCAIL Auto Extend Sampler, which&nbsp;&nbsp; replaces both Wan-SCAIL-To-Video node and Custom&nbsp; Sampler node. This node acts as a looping sampler.&nbsp;&nbsp; Here we configure the values just like the regular&nbsp; custom sampler, but with some additional settings.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The chunk length can be set higher, but should&nbsp; be within the models limit, which is 81 frames.&nbsp;&nbsp; The overlap is the number of frames from the&nbsp; previous chunk which is used as the anchor and&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'should not exceed SCAIL\'s limit of 5 frames. Set&nbsp; color transfer to true if you want the colors of&nbsp;&nbsp; the extension chunks, which exceeds 81 frames, to&nbsp; match with the previous chunks. And that\'s pretty&nbsp;&nbsp; much it for the sampler. Next is the SCAIL-2&nbsp; Identity Tracker. To use it, after we load the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reference image and driving video, we need to run&nbsp; the node so that both references get fed into the&nbsp;&nbsp; node for processing. Click the reference button&nbsp; to see the reference image for marking. And,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'click the driving button to see the first frame&nbsp; of the driving video also for marking. Hit clear&nbsp;&nbsp; to remove all existing bounding boxes. Click and&nbsp; drag on the image or canvas to set the b-boxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Here I am demonstrating how to do a multi subject&nbsp; reference editing. Click inside each box to&nbsp;&nbsp; select, and scale the box by clicking the white&nbsp; handles and drag. To move, click inside the box&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and drag to move to adjust the position. Do the&nbsp; same with the reference video. Hit the driving&nbsp;&nbsp; button and adjust as needed. You can also use&nbsp; points to select the subjects instead of b-boxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This, however, is still experimental and may&nbsp; not produce good enough results. Click on point&nbsp;&nbsp; and clear the marks. Select the points of the&nbsp; subjects by clicking on the image in sequence,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like so. Here we input our segmentation prompts&nbsp; so the model knows what to segment. Let\'s see&nbsp;&nbsp; how the point mark method works. As you can&nbsp; see, the colors are not unique to the subjects&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and this might cause trouble in matching the&nbsp; subjects in the image to the driving video.&nbsp;&nbsp; So, I will clear it and go back to use the&nbsp; bounding boxes. Okay, much better. And then&nbsp;&nbsp; the edits we just did will be routed to the&nbsp; sampler here. There is also some notes here&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for more details of the workflow. This workflow is&nbsp; actually taken from the nodes repo, but with minor&nbsp;&nbsp; adjustments, nothing major. Okay. Now let\'s see&nbsp; what is required to run this workflow. You need&nbsp;&nbsp; the latest Comfy release for certain nodes and&nbsp; functions to work correctly. And then you need&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the \'SCAIL Auto Extend\' node pack. Install&nbsp; it via Comfy\'s manager only. Copy this link,&nbsp;&nbsp; go to manager and click \'Install via Git URL\'.&nbsp; Then, paste the link and press confirm. After&nbsp;&nbsp; that just restart comfy and refresh the&nbsp; browser. And lastly, please do re-check&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the red annotations before running the flow. I&nbsp; hope you liked the video. Thanks for watching.'
